# Dashboard Rules (Next.js Admin)

## Purpose
Admin dashboard for managing map data.

## Responsibilities
- CRUD operations (places, categories, etc.)
- Form handling
- Data visualization for admin use

## Data Access (STRICT)
- MUST call backend API
- MUST NOT connect to PostgreSQL directly
- MUST NOT use Prisma

## API Usage
- Use fetch or axios
- Centralize API calls in src/lib/api.ts

## UI Rules
- Use simple UI (shadcn/ui or minimal components)
- Focus on functionality over design

## Structure
- Use feature-based structure:
  features/places/
  features/categories/

## Forms
- Use React Hook Form + Zod

## Forbidden
- Direct SQL queries
- Business logic duplication
- Heavy computation

## Performance
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Use simple state management

## Goal
- Fast internal tool, not polished UI